==========================
git branch - list all branches
git branch <branch_name> create new branch
git checkout <branch-name> switch to an existing branch

git checkout -b <branch name> to create and switch the branch
git switch <branch name0 switch to an existing branch>
git switch -c <branch name> to create and switch to a new branch

git branch -v - show the branches along with their latest commit 

git branch -a to list local and remote branches
git merge <branch name> merges another branches into current branch
git merge --no-ff <branch-name>

git merge --squash <branch -name> combine all branches commit s into a single commit
git log --oneline --graph  --all sisplay branch and merge history visually
git branch -d <branch - name> to delete the branch

git branch -D <branch name> - force delete a branch

